{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/matchinfoprotocol\/ispartialmatch"]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MatchInfoProtocol\/isPartialMatch","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"metadata":{"symbolKind":"property","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"isPartialMatch","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Property","extendedModule":"GLib","title":"isPartialMatch","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:4GLib17MatchInfoProtocolPAAE09isPartialB0Sbvp"},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Usually if the string passed to g_regex_match*() matches as far as","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it goes, but is too short to match the entire pattern, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"text":" is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"returned. There are circumstances where it might be helpful to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"distinguish this case from other cases in which there is no match.","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MatchInfoProtocol"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"isPartialMatch"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"},{"text":" { ","kind":"text"},{"text":"get","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" }","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Consider, for example, an application where a human is required to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"type in data for a field with specific formatting requirements. An"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"example might be a date in the form ddmmmyy, defined by the pattern"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"^\\d?\\d(jan|feb|mar|apr|may|jun|jul|aug|sep|oct|nov|dec)"},{"text":"\\d\\d$”.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If the application sees the user’s keystrokes one by one, and can"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"check that what has been typed so far is potentially valid, it is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"able to raise an error as soon as a mistake is made.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"GRegex supports the concept of partial matching by means of the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"partialSoft"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"partialHard","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" flags.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"When they are used, the return code for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_regex_match()"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"code":"g_regex_match_full()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is, as usual, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"for a complete match, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":" otherwise. But, when these functions"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"return "},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", you can check if the match was partial calling"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_match_info_is_partial_match()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The difference between ","type":"text"},{"code":"partialSoft","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"partialHard","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is that when a partial match is encountered"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"partialSoft"},{"type":"text","text":", matching continues to search for a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"possible complete match, while with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"partialHard"},{"text":" matching","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"stops at the partial match."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"When both "},{"code":"partialSoft","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"partialHard"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"are set, the latter takes precedence."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There were formerly some restrictions on the pattern for partial matching."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"The restrictions no longer apply.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pcrepartial(3)"},{"text":" for more information on partial matching.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MatchInfoProtocol/isPartialMatch":{"type":"topic","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"isPartialMatch","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Usually if the string passed to g_regex_match*() matches as far as","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"it goes, but is too short to match the entire pattern, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":" is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"returned. There are circumstances where it might be helpful to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"distinguish this case from other cases in which there is no match."}],"title":"isPartialMatch","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MatchInfoProtocol\/isPartialMatch","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/matchinfoprotocol\/ispartialmatch","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib","kind":"symbol","title":"GLib","abstract":[],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","role":"collection"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MatchInfoProtocol":{"role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MatchInfoProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"A GMatchInfo is an opaque struct used to return information about","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"matches."}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/matchinfoprotocol","title":"MatchInfoProtocol","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"MatchInfoProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MatchInfoProtocol"}}}